# What NOT to upload to Cloud Build. Keep models/*.onnx (runtime) + vlm-prompts.json (bundled).
.git/
.gitignore
.venv/
.venv-export/
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
.env
.env.local
.env.example
# transient eval/build artifacts (the committed model.onnx + *_calibration.json ARE needed)
models/eval_cache_*.pkl
models/*.log
# Big ONNX backbones (~420MB) are hosted on the HF Hub (dsreya/asli-onnx-backbones) and downloaded in
# the Dockerfile at build — keeping them OUT of the Cloud Build source upload (which otherwise times
# out at ~450MB / 300s on a home uplink). Small JSON calibrations stay in the upload.
models/clip-vit-b32/
models/dinov2-small/
# Same reasoning for the fine-tuned matchers: the container pulls them from the Hub on first warmup
# (GARMENT_HF_REPO / PROMISE_HF_REPO), so a locally-synced copy must not ride along in the upload.
models/garment-dinov2/
models/promise-dinov2/
# tests + one-off dev tooling — not needed in the serving image
test_*.py
gen_test_data.py
README.md

# Local Qdrant state — a running dev service holds these sqlite files open, which fails the source
# upload with PermissionError, and runtime state has no place in a serving image anyway.
qdrant_data/
